WEBVTT

00:06:55.863 --> 00:07:00.779
DK: Well, we started out asking
about judgment under uncertainty,

00:07:00.803 --> 00:07:03.403
that is, how people assess probabilities,

00:07:03.427 --> 00:07:06.016
how they make intuitive predictions

00:07:06.040 --> 00:07:08.420
and how they test hypotheses.

00:07:08.444 --> 00:07:09.857
CA: Give us an example.

00:07:09.881 --> 00:07:13.538
DK: I'll give you my best example,
actually, I think.

00:07:13.962 --> 00:07:17.915
It's a fairly complicated one,
but your listeners will follow.

00:07:18.616 --> 00:07:22.139
So suppose I ask you
to think about a woman --

00:07:22.163 --> 00:07:23.468
I'll call her Julie.

00:07:24.491 --> 00:07:26.678
I'll tell you two things about her:

00:07:26.702 --> 00:07:30.431
she's a graduating senior at a university